Imagine that your iPhone could be a skater, go through different circuits and avoid obstacles..

«The skater» is an augmented reality game where the player interactes with a virtual world using real cards and handmade origamis. In the eighties a young skater in Berlin tries to launch american skaters’ culture. Can you help him to reach this goal?

In a graphical universe, that recalls zine culture, every level is created by printed cards and virtual obstacles could be passed finding the right physical origamis. But don’t spend too much time to contemplate this paper city, the police is looking for you..

Design & Development: Andrea Rovescalli, Praiya Chinagarn, Solkin Keizer

Technologies: OpenFrameworks, OpenCV, OpenGl & Cinema4D